events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Bucks hadn't just been beating them, they were beating them easily.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 38, Knicks snap Bucks' seven-game winning streak with 129-122 victory

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic's frequent parade to the free-throw line was a sore subject for Steve Kerr.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic a perfect 18-of-18 from free-throw line, draws ire of Kerr, as Nuggets beat Warriors 120-114

events.name: Boston Celtics at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — The Boston Celtics were happy to share on Christmas Day, and it propelled them to a historic holiday against the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis, Celtics start strong in 126-115 Christmas Day win over Davis, Lakers

headlines.description: — The first thing Miami rookie Jaime Jaquez Jr. did when the schedule was released this summer was check to see when the Heat play in his hometown of Los Angeles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaime Jaquez Jr. scores 31, Spoelstra moves to 9-0 on Christmas as Heat top 76ers 119-113

headlines.description: — The Phoenix Suns ran double teams at Luka Doncic and the Dallas star picked them apart to set up easy baskets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 50 points to eclipse 10,000 for career, Mavericks beat Suns 128-114
